Michelangelo A. Volpi: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 29, 2017 12:52 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Index Ventures



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Michelangelo A. Volpi  Partner and General Partner, Index VenturesAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 24 Board Members in 24 different organizations across 30 different industries.See Board Relationships50--
Background

		Mr. Michelangelo A. Volpi, also known as Mike, has been Group Chief Executive Officer at Lloyds Bank Plc, Lloyds Banking Group Plc, HBOS plc and Bank Of Scotland plc since March 1, 2011. He has been a Partner at Index Ventures since July 2009. He joined the firm in 2009. Mr. Volpi served as the Chief Executive Officer at Alliance & Leicester plc from October 12, 2008 to December 1, 2010. Mr. Volpi led the investment by Index Ventures in Cloud.com (now part of Citrix). ... Prior to Index, he was the Chief Executive Officer at Joost He served as the Chief Executive Officer at Santander UK Plc at Banco Santander S.A and Banesto Banco Espanol de Credito SA from August 21, 2006 to December 1, 2010. He served as the Chief Executive Officer at Banco Santander Totta. He served as an Executive Vice President at Banco Santander S.A. Mr. Volpi joined Banco Santander S.A. in 1997 and served as its Executive Vice President of Portugal since June 2001. He served as an Executive Vice President of Santander Totta at Banco Santander, S.A. He served as the Chief Executive Officer at Banco Santander Brasil. From 1994, Mr. Volpi performed in various executive roles for 13 years at Cisco Systems. He served as the company's Chief Strategy Officer, where he was responsible for Cisco's corporate strategy as well as business development, strategic alliances, advanced Internet projects, legal services and government affairs. During this tenure, Mr. Volpi was instrumental in the creation of the company's acquisition and investment strategies, as Cisco acquired more than 70 companies. He began his career at Hewlett Packard's optoelectronics division. He then became Senior Vice President & General Manager of the Routing and Service Provider Technology Group, where he led Cisco's business for the Service Provider market and was also responsible for all of Cisco's routing products. Mr. Volpi serves as the Chairman at Banco Santander Portugal. Mr. Volpi is currently a director of Sonos, Soundcloud, Lookout, Path, Big Switch Networks, Zuora, Hortonworks and StorSimple. He is also on the board of Ericsson. He has been Independent Non-Executive Director of Exor N.V. since May 29, 2015. Mr. Volpi has been an Executive Director of Lloyds Bank plc and Lloyds Banking Group Plc since January 17, 2011. He has been Executive Director of HBOS Plc., since March 1, 2011. He has been a Director of Pure Storage, Inc. since April 2014. He has been an Executive Director of Bank of Scotland Plc since January 17, 2011. He serves as a Non-Executive Director of Fundação Champalimaud in and a Governor of London Business School. Mr. Volpi currently serves on the boards of Elastic, Confluent, Wealthfront, Interana and Skyport Systems. NetworksFrom June 1, 2009 to February 28, 2011, he served as a Non-Executive Director of Bank of England since June 1, 2009 to February 28, 2011. He served as an Executive Director of Alliance & Leicester Plc from October 12, 2008 to December 1, 2010. Mr. Volpi  served as a Non-Executive Director at Abbey National plc from December 1, 2004 to August 2006. He served as the Chairman of Banco Santander Totta, S.A. until 2011 and its Chief Executive Officer from 2000 to 2006. He served as an Executive Director of Santander UK plc from December 1, 2004 to December 1, 2010. He served as a Director of Santander Totta. In 2015, he was Chairman of the Wallace Collection by the Prime Minister. He was an Assistant Professor at the Universidade Catolica Portuguesa. In 2014, the Government of Portugal awarded António with the Order of Merit Grã-Cruz, which is the highest Order of Civil Merit. In June 2011, he was awarded an Honorary Doctorate from the University of Edinburgh and in July 2012 he was awarded an Honorary Doctorate from the University of Bath. Mr. Volpi earned a B.S. in Mechanical Engineering in 1988, an M.S. in Manufacturing Systems Engineering in 1989 and an M.B.A. from Stanford University in 1994.Read Full Background




Corporate Headquarters
